## Psychological Experiments and Terrorism

- **Milgram Experiment:** Demonstrates obedience to authority as a factor in committing harmful acts.
- **Stanford Prison Experiment:** Highlights how social roles and group dynamics can lead to abusive behavior.
- These experiments suggest that ordinary individuals can commit atrocities under certain social conditions ([Pittala, 2017](https://medium.com/@sadhanapittala/why-do-people-join-terrorist-groups-9b6f3e6f6e2b)).

