## Motivations Behind Joining Terrorist Groups: Case Studies

### Islamic State (ISIS)

Research categorizes ISIS recruits into nine groups based on motivations:

| Motivation Type      | Description                                                                                   |
|---------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Status Seekers      | Seeking social recognition or financial gain                                                 |
| Revenge Seekers     | Responding to perceived oppression or injustice                                              |
| Identity Seekers    | Searching for belonging and purpose                                                          |
| Redemption Seekers  | Seeking to atone for past wrongs                                                             |
| Thrill Seekers      | Attracted by excitement and adventure                                                        |
| Responsibility Seekers | Joining for financial support to family                                                      |
| Justice Seekers     | Fighting perceived injustice                                                                 |
| Death Seekers       | Suicidal individuals seeking honorable death                                                |

This diversity illustrates the multifaceted nature of terrorist recruitment ([Pittala, 2017](https://medium.com/@sadhanapittala/why-do-people-join-terrorist-groups-9b6f3e6f6e2b)).

### Tamil Tigers (LTTE)

The LTTE emerged from ethnic marginalization and political exclusion of Tamils in Sri Lanka, recruiting mainly from marginalized youth who felt denied opportunities ([Pittala, 2017](https://medium.com/@sadhanapittala/why-do-people-join-terrorist-groups-9b6f3e6f6e2b)).

